pipelines.name: github-check
pipelines.description:
Newly uploaded patchsets on GitHub enter this pipeline to receive an
initial +/-1 Verified vote. Should be used by production ready jobs,
for experimental ones github-manual pipeline.

pipelines.name: github-manual
pipelines.description:
Used for testing new or experimental jobs by manually trigerring them
with magic comment `check-github`.

pipelines.name: check
pipelines.description:
Newly uploaded patchsets enter this pipeline to receive an
initial +/-1 Verified vote.

pipelines.name: gate
pipelines.description:
Changes that have been approved by core developers are enqueued
in order in this pipeline, and if they pass tests, will be
merged.

pipelines.name: post
pipelines.description: This pipeline runs jobs that operate after each change is merged.

pipelines.name: pre-release
pipelines.description: When a commit is tagged with a pre-release tag, this pipeline runs jobs that publish archives and documentation.

pipelines.name: release
pipelines.description: When a commit is tagged as a release, this pipeline runs jobs that publish archives and documentation.

pipelines.name: periodic
pipelines.description: Jobs in this queue are triggered daily.

pipelines.name: experimental
pipelines.description: On-demand pipeline for requesting a run against a set of jobs that are not yet gating. Leave review comment of "check experimental" to run jobs in this pipeline.

pipelines.name: merge-check
pipelines.description: Each time a change merges, this pipeline verifies that all open changes on the same project are still mergeable.
